Home Assistant custom integration. HACS compatible.

## Install

### HACS (recommended)

1. HACS → Integrations → ⋮ → Custom repositories
2. Add `https://github.com/{{ github_user }}/{{ project_slug }}` as **Integration**
3. Install **{{ component_friendly_name }}**
4. Restart Home Assistant
5. Settings → Devices & Services → Add Integration → search **{{ component_friendly_name }}**

### Manual

```bash
cd /config/custom_components
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_user }}/{{ project_slug }} {{ component_slug }}
# Restart HA
```

## Configuration

UI-driven via config flow. No YAML required.

